==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Archi-
<hw>Ar"chi-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., <ets>archi-</ets>, Gr.
<grk>'archi-</grk>, a prefix which is from the same root as
<grk>'a`rchein</grk> to be first, to begin; <grk>'archh</grk> the first
place, beginning; <grk>'archo`s</grk> chief. Cf. AS. <ets>arce-</ets>,
<ets>erce-</ets>, OHG. <ets>erzi-</ets>, G. <ets>erz-</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A prefix signifying <xex>chief</xex>, <xex>arch</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>archi</ex>tect, <ex>archi</ex>episcopal</as>. In <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
and <fld>(Anat.)</fld> it usually means <xex>primitive</xex>,
<xex>original</xex>, <xex>ancestral</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>archi</ex>pterygium, the primitive fin or wing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Archiannelida</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
